Merge pull request #20 from macreery/non-halting-event-processing

@aaw: Non-halting event processing
Add deprecation comment

Don't halt event processing on an undefined attribute.

When an event matches a global handler (defined in config/schema.json), we
don't want to halt execution if one of the attributes in a single handler
is undefined. (If an attribute referenced in an inline handler is undefined,
we will still halt execution.)

As an example case, updated the following/unfollowing schema definitions to
accept either "followed" or "followee" as the followee parameter. We can
remove the former handler once client applications' code goes to production.
Fix Procfile port for local Resque web worker

Merge pull request #19 from macreery/counter-updates

@aaw: Improvements around counters and /sync

Modified logic for gross counters

Instead of incrementing an integer on every ZADD operation to a Flux set,
we now use a HyperLogLog counter to track the number of distinct key-score
pairs added to a set.

This aligns somewhat better with our expected client use case, where clients
may "replay" events back into Flux by specifying a canonical score per event.
Add support for intersection and union counts on sets via HyperLogLog

A couple improvements around /sync

* Properly emancipate Redis after sync
* Swap app/Resque database numbers so that app database matches master
